message.text: Ich nenne ihn Agip. Er ist Deutscher. Er hat einen Migrationshintergrund. Sein Opa wurde vor vielen, vielen Jahren zur Wirtschaftswunder Zeit in das Land geholt. Er integrierte sich schnell, lernte seine Frau kennen und sie lebten fort an in diesem Land. Bekamen Kinder und Enkel. Einer von diesen Enkeln ist Agip . Er ist in Deutschland geboren, hat aber keine deutschen Wurzeln. In dem Land seiner Vorfahren ist er fremd. Agip erzählte mir, dass er das Gefühl hat, in keinem Land wirklich dazuzugehören. Es ist ein Gefühl wie. „ZWISCHEN DEN STÜHLEN“ zu sitzen.

items.text:
🎬 CASTING CALL – STUDENT FILM
The Man Who Came Back From the Future

Hi! My name is Yuri Kakuya, and I’m currently a student in the Foundation Program at Vancouver Film School.

We are looking for 3 roles for our final project.

⸻

🎭 ROLES

JACK (Male, preferably in his 30s–40s)

A character who exists simultaneously as the screenwriter of the film, its director, and the patient who watches it.

JESSICA (Female, preferably in her 20s)

A character who exists as a figure within Jack’s film, the actress portraying that figure, and Jack’s attending physician.

THE MAN (Male, preferably in his 20s)

A character who exists as a man who has returned from the future, the actor portraying him, and Jack’s attending physician.

⸻

📖 STORYLINE

A filmmaker documents a theory about time through a man who has already seen himself commit a murder in the future.

As past, present, and future overlap across film sets, performances, and memories, the man realizes that knowing the future may be the very thing that erases his freedom—turning choice into inevitability, and life into a film whose ending is already written.

This project is built on the concepts of metacognition and fractal structure, functioning as a cinematic apparatus that allows the audience to re-experience a central question:

Can a future that is already perceived still be called the future?

Through allegory and symbolic dialogue, the characters guide the viewer into this experiential inquiry.

⸻

📩 SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS

Please submit your video audition to:

📧 recognizedtime@gmail.com

In your email, please indicate which role you are interested in.

⸻

⚠️ IMPORTANT NOTES

 • This is a student film, non-union, and unpaid (volunteer).

 • All cast members will receive screen credit.

 • Final rehearsals will begin one week before the first day of shooting.

 • This project is planned to be registered on IMDb.

 • Meals provided on set.

⸻

📅 KEY DATES

 • Audition Deadline: February 15, 2026

 • Callbacks: Vancouver Film School February 21, 2026

 • Shooting Day: March 7 and 8, 2026

⸻

🎥 PRODUCTION INFO

 • UNION: Student Film / Non-union / Unpaid

 • FORMAT: 2160/24p, 4K (Sony FX3)

 • SHOOTING LOCATION: Vancouver, BC

 • SCRIPT AVAILABILITY: Via email

If you’re interested in this project, feel free to email me!

I’m happy to share the full screenplay with you.

Best,

Yuri Kakuya

📧 recognizedtime@gmail.com

**CASTING CALL - Commercial **

We are looking for actors for a product branding shoot for a Balance of Nature commercial. 

**Who we’re looking for:**
* Female & Male Talent Ages 50+
* Female & Male Talent Ages 30+
* Children ages 5+
* All ethnicities encouraged to apply
* Comfortable on camera and able to interact naturally together

**Shoot details:**
* Location: St. George, UT
* Date(s): End of February
* Compensation: $65-$85/hr depending on experience. Travel covered, if necessary. 
* Usage: Brand marketing and advertising materials. **Freelance preferred.**

**To submit:**
Please send recent headshots, names and ages, location, and contact information to *abustillo@bonadmin.com* with the subject line **“Casting Call".**

Thank you!

Hello!

LOOKING FOR EXTRAS

We’re filming a retirement party scene for our indie horror feature HACKJOB and looking for party attendees to help fill out the outdoor venue.

Date: Monday, Feb. 16th, 2026
-Old Town Scottsdale, AZ (will give the location via email)
-Approx. 7–10pm
-All ages welcome
-Attire: cocktail / nice dinner / gala vibes (not black tie)
-Food provided

You don’t need to be there the entire time — mainly for the wide group shots, mingling, enjoying the party, and listening to a speech given by the man of the hour, Christoper Hooper, played by Bourke Floyd. 

You're more than welcome to bring/invite others, just let me know so we can keep a head count. 

If you’re interested and available, shoot me an email at: luca2babyfaces@gmail.com

items.text:
Friends!

The Film Program at Cinematic Arts at CCA (formerly The Colorado Film School) invites actors of all ages to participate in our Spring 2026 Open Auditions!

Our student filmmakers are casting for a wide range of short films, narrative projects, and cinematic productions, and we are seeking performers of all backgrounds, ages, and experience levels to help bring these stories to life on screen.

Whether you are a seasoned professional, a student, or someone who simply loves acting, you are warmly invited to audition and collaborate with the next generation of filmmakers.

📅 Audition Dates & Times

Friday, February 6, 2026

🕙 10:00 a.m. – 5:00 p.m.

Saturday, February 7, 2026

🕙 10:00 a.m. – 4:00 p.m.

 

📍 Location

Lowry Studios – Community College of Aurora

9075 E. Lowry Blvd.

Denver, CO 80230

 

🎭 What to Prepare

Please bring a 2–3 minute prepared monologue for your primary audition.

In addition to the main audition, we will also host Satellite Auditions for specific student film productions:

• These will take place in rooms throughout the building

• Auditions are first-come, first-served

• Actors can sign up to cold read for individual projects

• We anticipate up to 10 productions casting during this event

• A list of roles and productions will be available on the day of the audition

• Participation in satellite auditions is optional, but highly encouraged

 

📝 How to Sign Up

Actors can sign up using the QR code on the flyer or by visiting:

Accessible Web Link:

https://www.ccaurora.edu/open-auditions

(For visually impaired users or anyone unable to scan the QR code, this link provides full access to the sign-up form.)

If you can't find a reserved space that works for you, come anyway during your preferred time. We will work you into the schedule!

We can't wait to see you this Friday or Saturday!

 

📩 Questions?

Please contact:

galina.boulgakova@ccaurora.edu

 🎥 Help our students tell their stories through the magic of cinema.

topComments.text: I’m sorry but this should be posted a minimum of two weeks in advance so that we can plan and prepare for this. Posting this a day before when most of us have either booked ourselves on other agreements or just unavailable due to some other reason does not help either party involved.
I’m at 11:30am on Saturday. Highly recommend attending this. I’ve done 5 student films.

Już za dwa dni, w czwartek 12 lutego o godzinie 18:00, drzwi naszej warsztatowi artystycznej Z Miłości Do otworzą się jak szeroko! Zapraszamy osoby w wieku nastoletniem (11–17 lat) na wyjątkowe warsztaty musicalowe! Tego dnia zajęcia są całkowicie darmowe, więc to idealna okazja, żeby przekonać się, jak pracujemy, i dołączyć do naszej niesamowitej grupy musicalowej.

Śpiew, aktorstwo i taniec. Spotkania odbywają się co tydzień i trwają dwie godziny. To nie tylko nauka, ale przede wszystkim szansa na rozwijanie swoich talentów w przyjaznej atmosferze, poznanie nowych przyjaciół i przeżycie czegoś naprawdę wyjątkowego.

Nie czekaj, miejsca są limited! Zapisz się już teraz przez formularz kontaktowy na stronie www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt

items.text:
**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk ) ‘’Sensualny gotyk’’**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator. Tematem sesji będzie sensualny gotyk.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 20 - 50 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw to kobieta w selsualnym gotyku. Mile widziane panie, które posiadają jakieś ciekawe stroję gotyckie. ** Ja natomiast mam różne gadżety pod otoczenie typu: świeczniki, skrzynki czy nawet kałamarz a nawet nóż do listów w stylu średniowiecznym.**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk ) ‘’Anioł’’**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator. Tematem sesji będzie sensualny Anioł.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 20 - 50 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

items.text:
CASTING CALL - SHORT FILM - UNPAID

No Prior Experience Required

Genre: Realist Drama

Location: Liverpool

Shoot dates: Saturday 20th June & Sunday 21st June

Sunday Roast is about how a family that has been dysfunctional for years reacts to the introduction of an outsider. Actor-led and dialogue driven, this is a film about the uncomfortable moments that we all put up with in order to get by in life.

If you’re interested in any of the below roles please contact me at [sundayroastshort@gmail.com](mailto:sundayroastshort@gmail.com). Please send headshots and showreels if you have them.

SHARON (40s)
Sharon is a woman who has learned to survive by keeping everything in motion. She believes it is her responsibility as a mother to look after her family, even when it costs her personally. At her core she wants only her family’s happiness.
Her relationship with her mother is the central wound of her adult life. She knows exactly where it hurts, but she also knows that naming it only deepens the pain. So she gets on with life, convinced this is the only way to get by

NAN (60s-70s)
Nan is socially adept, affectionate, and completely blind to the harm she causes. She is the family matriarch and commands unquestioned respect, even in her most irrational moments. She does not see herself as cruel; in her mind, she is honest, wise, and entitled to her views.
Her power is quiet and absolute. She never raises her voice or argues. The family has been circling her moods for decades.

LAUREN (mid-late 20s)
Lauren is socially intelligent and emotionally open. She arrives wanting to do the right thing, to help and to fit in. As the meal goes on, she begins to understand that the politeness in this family is not neutral, it’s the core of the problem.
She is the only person not fully accustomed to this dynamic. She sees through it all, but is unable to change anything.

STEVEN (40s–early 50s)

Steven is a typical dad. He loves his wife and understands her pain, but he has long ago decided that stepping in only makes things worse. H.e tries to keep the peace, and to keep things light-hearted. As a father he is warm and genuinely caring. He believes the family still works because he keeps things light. In his own way, he allows things to continue as they are.

ALEX (mid–late 20s)

Alex has grown up inside a dysfunctional family and learned how to survive it. He uses humour to cut through tense moments. He wants everyone to be okay, but has never seriously imagined that things could be different.
He loves his partner Lauren and is proud to bring her home, but he is unprepared for what it means to let someone truly see his family.

Just a couple of lessons in! My beginner adults are smashing it in Liverpool every:

Monday 6.30-7.30pm
Thursday 7-8pm

If you’d like to give it a try then come along! Your first session is free and this class is for ABSOLUTE BEGINNERS!! (Some of these guys have NEVER danced before!) 

I can guarantee that you’ll leave with a smile on your face and a spring in your step! 😁🙌

DM/email for more info and to claim your spot!

NATIONALLY SYNDICATED COURT SHOW IS LOOKING FOR MARRIED & LONG-TERM COUPLES WHO WANT HELP OR CLOSURE

A nationally syndicated court show is seeking real married couples and long-term partners who are on the verge of breaking up and need answers, resolution, or closure.

We are especially interested in couples with years of history and real-life stakes, including shared children, finances, property, or businesses.

Are you and your spouse facing any of the following?

• Are you married and ready to call it quits, but need answers first?

• Do you suspect your spouse or long-term partner is cheating?

• Is your spouse accusing you of cheating and/or denying your child?

• Have years of marriage led you to a breaking point where you need closure?

• Do you have evidence your spouse or long-term partner has been unfaithful and want to confront them?

• Is your spouse’s behavior tearing your family or marriage apart?

• Are bad habits or addictions damaging your marriage and affecting your children?

• Have ongoing trust issues made it impossible to move forward in your marriage?

• Are in-laws or extended family interfering in your marriage?

• Are you in a long-term marriage with unresolved financial betrayal or disputes?

• Are you married with children and need answers for the sake of your family’s future?

• Have you reached the final straw in a long-term marriage and need resolution?

WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

• Married couples

• Engaged couples

• Long-term couples (4+ years preferred) with real stakes involved

• Shared children

• Shared finances

• Shared property (home, apartment, vehicles)

• Shared business or major life commitments

• LGBTQ+ married and long-term couples

WHAT’S INCLUDED:

• One-day court show appearance

• Couples counseling / marriage counseling support

• Lie detector testing (if applicable)

• DNA testing (if applicable)

👉 All testing and services are provided and paid for by production.

Click the link below or copy and paste to bowser 

[https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/](https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/)
items.title: Seeking Married/Long Term Couples in Relationships NATIONWIDE CASTING

items.text:
I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that’s been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we’ll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you’d like the free advice of some of Britain’s top lawyers (likely in region of £10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**** We cannot dispute anything against councils - this would be a person to person claim - we have also reached out capacity for car cases and rogue traders ****

items.text: We are currently casting for our upcoming virtual production of ‘King Lear’ directed by myself and colin albo. We would love to see lots of new talent, please do fill out the audition form if interested and send over your headshot/resume to the email provided. Any questions ask away below!

sharedPost.text:
AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT

King Lear by William Shakespeare

A Virtual Staged Reading
Presented by Curtain Call Virtual Productions

Curtain Call Virtual Productions is proud to announce auditions for a virtual staged reading of William Shakespeare’s monumental tragedy King Lear.

Audition Date:
Sunday, February 22nd
7:30 p.m. BST / 2:30 p.m. EST / 11:30 a.m. PST

Held Virtually (via Zoom)

PRODUCTION TEAM
Co-Directed by: Colin Albo & Ashley Marsh

Original Script by: William Shakespeare

Edits & Language Modernization by: Colin Albo

HOW TO REGISTER
To register for auditions, participants must complete both of the following steps:

Email your headshot and theatrical résumé to

curtaincallvirtualproductions@gmail.com

Fill out the audition form linked on either the event page or the Facebook announcement

Once registration is complete, all auditioning actors will receive an email containing a PDF of the audition sides, which will be read during the audition.

No advanced preparation is required.

This is a staged reading, and multiple roles will be doubled.

All roles are open unless otherwise noted.

Please note: the role of Oswald has already been cast.

Important note: Due to the violence and mature content contained throughout the play, absolutely nobody under the age of 18 is allowed to audition! Absolutely no exceptions!

ROLES AVAILABLE
King Lear
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 40s–Early 60s
The aging King of Britain whose decision to divide his kingdom based on his daughters’ professions of love sets the tragedy in motion. His journey from absolute authority to madness and painful self-knowledge is the heart of the play.

Goneril
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s–Mid 30s
Lear’s eldest daughter; ruthless, power-hungry, and manipulative. Married to the Duke of Albany. Embodies cruelty and ingratitude.

Regan
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s–Early 30s
Lear’s middle daughter; equally cruel, often more sadistic than Goneril. Married to the Duke of Cornwall. Acts as Goneril’s partner in stripping Lear of power and dignity.

Cordelia
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens–Early 20s
Lear’s youngest daughter; honest, principled, and loving despite her refusal to flatter him. Marries the King of France and becomes Queen of France. Represents moral truth and emotional integrity.
Doubles as: The Fool — Lear’s companion and truth-teller who uses wit and riddles to expose harsh truths.

Gloucester
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Early 40s–Late 60s
A nobleman whose story parallels Lear’s: a father misjudging his children. Father of Edmund and Edgar. His blinding and suffering mirror Lear’s descent into madness.

Edmund
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens–Early 20s
Gloucester’s illegitimate son; ambitious, clever, and morally corrupt. A driving antagonist whose manipulation fuels much of the play’s violence.

Edgar
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s–Late 30s
Gloucester’s legitimate son; loyal, moral, and forced into disguise as “Poor Tom” to help his father. Represents endurance, redemption, and survival.

Albany
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s–Mid 30s
Goneril’s husband. Albany begins the play restrained and politically cautious, overshadowed by stronger personalities. As the kingdom fractures, he develops a moral spine, ultimately rejecting cruelty and asserting principled leadership. Doubles as: Doctor, Knight, Curan

Cornwall
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s–Early 30s
Regan’s spouse and a ruthless enforcer of authority. Impulsive, violent, and tyrannical, Cornwall embodies unchecked authoritarianism and the danger of power without empathy. Doubles as: Gentleman, Herald, Old Man

Kent
Supporting Role | Any Gender | Playing Age: Late 40s–Early 60s
A fiercely loyal noble and trusted advisor to Lear. Blunt, principled, and courageous to the point of self-sacrifice, Kent is banished for speaking truth to power and disguises themself to continue serving Lear in exile. Doubles as: Duke of Burgundy, Messenger

Oswald (CAST)
Supporting Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Any Age
Goneril’s primary servant. Endlessly obedient, Oswald follows any and all instructions from his mistress without considering their moral implications, rendering him cruel and heartless in her shadow.
Doubles as: King of France, Servant 1

NOTE: This show and all other productions by this company are unpaid at this time

Performers of all backgrounds are encouraged to audition.

This production embraces non-traditional casting and aims to assemble a strong ensemble to explore the power, cruelty, and humanity at the heart of King Lear.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScHMbtYTBlReh1AvrRsYaDtGR0nPaMaNMleJO2BZIw-D4quWw/viewform?usp=header

sharedPost.text:
---

🌀🎬🎥🌚 Exclusive Acting Workshop – Final Version .version A.

VERY LOW COST: One-on-One Online via Skype

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

🎬 Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

🌐 International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

🌐 IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

🌐 Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

🤔 What You Will Learn:

🌀 Emotional Range: Master the ability to express a full spectrum of emotions, making your performances more believable and compelling.

🌀 Character Development: Create rich, multidimensional characters by exploring their internal world, external actions, and backstory.

🌀 Method Acting: Use personal experiences and emotions to deliver raw, authentic performances.

🌀 Working with Directors and Crew: Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate with crew members to enhance your performance.

🌀 Scene Preparation: Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

🌀 Industry Standards: How to create a professional showreel and work effectively with casting directors and filmmakers.

---

🎬 Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski’s Approach)

🔹 Breaking a Scene Down: The use of internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

Character Exercise: The Hitman’s First Kill

📍 Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter’s midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed—a brand-new sniper rifle.

🔹 Exercise 1 (Singular Emotion): Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target. Remain fully in character.

🔹 Exercise 2 (Multiple Emotional Shifts):

1. Enter slightly out of breath, feeling relief—"I made it here. No one saw me."

2. The weight of reality sets in—"Am I really about to kill someone?"

3. Mesmerized by the artistry of the gun—draw on memories of seeing/touching weapons.

4. Snapped back to reality by a siren—trace the feeling of waking from a dream.

5. Decision made—move to the window, set up the gun, and wait.

🔹 Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set with actors who never broke character—even during dinner.

Exercise 3 (If Time Allows): The Phone Call

📍 Scene: You’ve done something terrible—enough to make the person you love most leave forever. You must convince them to stay.

🎭 Goal: Improvise, using pure emotional truth, until the performance is undeniably real.

---

🎬 Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

🔹 Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character’s mind.

Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

📍 Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated—until suddenly, you’re holding an AK-47. (Note: These scenes are purely acting exercises. They can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)

🔹 Alternative Scene: A character about to detonate a bomb, written in the style of Heath Ledger’s Joker.

🔹 Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most—telling them why. (Scripted or improv.)

📍 Final Monologue Exercise: "Hi everyone… Tomorrow’s going to be different." The last words before an irreversible decision.

🔹 Accents: Versatility in performance—working with British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents.

🔹 Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness—sit before the camera, smiling, at total peace. Convey pure serenity.

---

🎬 Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

🔹 Understanding Your Role: How an actor fits into the filmmaking process.

🔹 Hitting Marks & Lighting: The technical side of making performances shine.

🔹 Shooting Ratios: How they affect your performance.

🔹 Crew Collaboration: Understanding continuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

Final Showreel Scenes (Day 3):

🎭 Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it? You really think that?" (Improv)

🎭 Heartbroken: "But I didn’t mean it... please, please, don’t leave me…" (Improv)

🎭 Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc², then time versus chaos... who cares?" (Improv)

🎭 Flat & Emotionless: "We’re born, we live, we die. That’s it." (Improv)

🔹 Goal: Draw from personal experiences and trace memories to make the performances deeply real.

---

🎬 Day 4: Fear and Survival – Personal Experience & Character Creation

🔹 Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape

📍 Scene: You’re lost in the jungle at night, exhausted, your breath the only sound. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out—pleading for help. No answer.

🎭 Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death – the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation – the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion – feeling your body give in.

🎭 Method Process:

1. Internal Visualization – Close your eyes, hear the insects, the rustling leaves, your pounding heartbeat.

2. Personal Connection – Recall a moment when you felt completely lost or afraid.

3. Scene Execution – Let the emotions guide your body and voice.

Exercise 2: The Phone Call Redux

📍 Scene: You’re on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it’s over. What do you say? What do you leave out?

🎭 Objective: Make the desperation feel real. This is life or death.

---

Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they’ve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

---

🎬🎥 Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

This isn’t just a class—it’s an intense, immersive experience that will change the way you act forever.

🌐 To Enroll: p.m.me or e.mail:

mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let’s create something unforgettable.

Paid Casting Call - Sun 15th Feb

Hi all,
We’re looking for supporting artists to be customers and walking pedestrians for a scene at a restaurant in the Wilmslow area of Manchester on the 15th of February. The length of the shoot is estimated to be 5 hours and start time required depends on the role. The dress code is “smart, date night” attire and supporting artists will need to supply their own attire. 

•Customers 17:00-22:00 
•Waiter 17:00-22:00 
•Pedestrians 19:00-00:00 

As we are working on a limited budget with all proceeds going towards children’s cancer charities and hospitals we can pay each artist at a rate of £12.21 per hour.

Hi all,
We’re looking for supporting artists to be customers and walking pedestrians for a scene at a restaurant in the Wilmslow area of Manchester on the 15th of February. The length of the shoot is estimated to be 5 hours and start time required depends on the role. The dress code is “smart, date night” attire and supporting artists will need to supply their own attire.

items.text:
VOICE ACTING CASTING CALL

I’m currently working on an exciting project for an audio installation in London, and we are looking to cast for some voice roles - which will involved reading short letters (approx 1 min of long audio for each role) demonstrating the impact of conflict during the Second World War on young people. 

Specifically, we are seeking:

* Boy aged 9-11 with Irish Accent (Dublin suits the material)
* Girl aged 14-16 with Scottish accent (Edinburgh accent would suit the material)

This is a paid opportunity. We are open to submissions from experienced actors as well as individuals who may not have formal acting experience.

If you are interested and would like to put yourself forward, please email pete.roch@squeakypedal.co.uk with the subject line CONFLICT IN CHILDHOOD CASTING.

Please include:
* Your name/ guardians name:
* Contact information
* A short audio clip

The deadline for submissions is Friday 13th February 2025.

If you have any questions or would like to discuss further, feel free to reach out, and one of our team can get in touch at a convenient time.

Thank you so much!

Pete Roch
Co-Founder, Squeaky Pedal

🎬 CASTING CALL – HEIGHTS OF DECEPTION 🎬

✨ AVAILABLE ROLE ✨
LANDON (African American Male, 50s)
Landon is an ex husband and a father shaped by regret and growth. He’s learning how to show up with warmth, patience, and intention—working to rebuild what was lost while protecting what still matters.

Character Traits:
• Emotionally complex
• Regret-aware but growth-oriented
• Truth-seeking
• Capable of warmth and confrontation
• Learning when to fight and when to listen

📍 Location: Louisville, KY

✔️ Be comfortable with dramatic, emotionally driven material

items.text:
ACTOR-MUSOS! **WELL PAID** ONGOING WORK WITH A FABULOUS TEAM!!

The Tailors Surprise Singers are looking for new guitarists who sing to join our team. We are VERY different from normal surprise singing groups - because we change all the lyrics to be about the guests! This personalised comedy approach makes for a fantastic and unique experience for them AND us.

Check out our viral Instagram @thetailorsuk for an insight into how we work. Previous clients include Jamie Oliver, Emma Bunton, Jamie Laing and Emily Maitlis.

Most gigs are paid at £325-£400 with travel and food all sorted. Must be London based with good availability over summer weekends.

Please email apply@the-tailors.co.uk with at least one video of you singing and playing guitar to be considered! (Just commenting on this post will not be considered an application but please do tag friends!) Next step if suitable will be a self tape request, then a workshop audition on the 3rd March in London.

items.text:
CASTING CALL LITTLE STEPS I NEVER SAW
📍The North East England📍Filming 18th-28th February 2026 🎥

* We are looking for a male in their late 40s-70 year old to play the old man in the film

* We’re a small group of passionate Student Filmmakers in our final year of Sunderland University. Looking for actors who, like us, want to get into the industry and or professional actors who want to help out the little guys. 🎬

📍The production is based in Tynemouth in the North East of England

The Film explores the deep emotions surrounding loss and the blessing of watching your child grow up in front of your eyes. ‘The Little Steps I never Saw’ is a psychological, Liminal Realism and Poetic Fantasy story that is deeply routed in symbolism and mystery.

This role will be UNPAID. However we will pay for all travel expenses 🚝 and good food will be provided on set. 🍕

⚠️Note: this film will be submitted into film festival’s 🎉

Contact: 📞

georgia.dodsworth24@gmail.com

❗️Please be prepared to provide a photo of yourself❗️📸

Sounddesigner · Filmkomponist · Audio Engineer
Hallo zusammen,

Ich arbeite in der Postproduktion für Film & Bewegtbild und unterstütze aktuell Projekte in Postproduktion oder kurz vor Picture Lock.

Leistungen:

• 🎬 Sounddesign & Atmos

• 🎼 Filmmusik / musikalische Untermalung

• 🎙️ Dialogediting & Cleanup

• 🎧 Stereo-Mix

Viele Grüße

Francesco

sharedPost.text:
Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 6/2026

DÜSTERE ZWISCHENWELTEN, DER GEHEIMTIPP AUS SÜDKOREA UND AUSGRABUNGEN IN ST PÖLTEN 

Die Gamingwelt war skeptisch als vor einigen Jahren ein Konsolenspiel zum Gruselhit in den Kinos avancierte. Doch aktuell schickt sich eine weitere Fortsetzung mit RETURN TO SILENT HILL an, erneut das Schaudern auf die Kinoleinwand zu bringen.

Seit dem Oscargewinner Parasite hat das koreanische Kino Hochkonjunktur. Mit dem Streifen NO OTHER CHOICE gelangt ein weiterer Film in die Kinos, dem sogar Oscarchancen eingeräumt werden. Ob der Film hält was er verspricht erzählt Ihnen unsere Filminsiderin Sarah Fuchs.

Clasien Swierstrak organisiert das EU XXL WANDERKINO in Wolkersdorf. Wir konnten mit der Lady, deren Wurzeln aus Holland sind, ein paar Worte wechseln. Über historische Ausgrabungen in St Pölten erzählt die Doku NEKROPOLIS. Wir konnten mit dem Regisseur,  Alexander Mitterecker dazu ein Interview führen. 

Abgerundet wird die Sendung wie immer mit Musik aus den Soundtracks der letzten 85 Jahre.

Mittwoch 4.2.2026 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

items.text:
EVC Talent Casting Show 2026 – Jetzt bewerben und Teil einer außergewöhnlichen Show werden

Die EVC Talent Casting Show startet 2026 in eine neue, spannende Staffel und bietet Künstlerinnen und Künstlern erneut eine Bühne, um sich einem breiten Publikum zu präsentieren. Der Auftakt der neuen Staffel ist für das Frühjahr 2026 geplant. Bewerbungen sind ab sofort möglich.

Gesucht werden Talente aus allen künstlerischen Bereichen: Musikerinnen und Musiker, Bands, Tänzerinnen und Tänzer (Solo, Duo oder Gruppe), Artistinnen und Artisten, Comedians sowie Menschen mit außergewöhnlichen oder besonderen Fähigkeiten. Ganz gleich, ob Sie bereits Bühnenerfahrung haben, als etablierte Künstlerin oder etablierter Künstler tätig sind, nach einer kreativen Pause wieder durchstarten möchten oder Ihr Talent zum ersten Mal vor Publikum zeigen entscheidend ist Ihre Leidenschaft und Begeisterung für das, was Sie tun.

Die EVC Talent Casting Show versteht sich als Plattform zur Förderung von Nachwuchstalenten ebenso wie zur Unterstützung etablierter Künstlerinnen und Künstler und kreativer Persönlichkeiten, die neue Impulse suchen. Teilnehmen können Kinder, Jugendliche und Erwachsene ab 6 Jahren. Minderjährige benötigen die Begleitung eines Erwachsenen.

Wenn Sie Ihr Talent präsentieren und unsere Jury überzeugen möchten, bewerben Sie sich jetzt online unter:
https://electricvisionscleve.de/casting.html

Wir freuen uns auf zahlreiche Bewerbungen und darauf, viele beeindruckende Talente kennenzulernen.

items.summary:
EVC Talent Casting Show 2026 – Jetzt bewerben und Teil einer außergewöhnlichen Show werden

Die EVC Talent Casting Show startet 2026 in eine neue, spannende Staffel und bietet Künstlerinnen und Künstlern erneut eine Bühne, um sich einem breiten Publikum zu präsentieren. Der Auftakt der neuen Staffel ist für das Frühjahr 2026 geplant. Bewerbungen sind ab sofort möglich.

Gesucht werden Talente aus allen künstlerischen Bereichen: Musikerinnen und Musiker, Bands, Tänzerinnen und Tänzer (Solo, Duo oder Gruppe), Artistinnen und Artisten, Comedians sowie Menschen mit außergewöhnlichen oder besonderen Fähigkeiten. Ganz gleich, ob Sie bereits Bühnenerfahrung haben, als etablierte Künstlerin oder etablierter Künstler tätig sind, nach einer kreativen Pause wieder durchstarten möchten oder Ihr Talent zum ersten Mal vor Publikum zeigen entscheidend ist Ihre Leidenschaft und Begeisterung für das, was Sie tun.

Die EVC Talent Casting Show versteht sich als Plattform zur Förderung von Nachwuchstalenten ebenso wie zur Unterstützung etablierter Künstlerinnen und Künstler und kreativer Persönlichkeiten, die neue Impulse suchen. Teilnehmen können Kinder, Jugendliche und Erwachsene ab 6 Jahren. Minderjährige benötigen die Begleitung eines Erwachsenen.

Wenn Sie Ihr Talent präsentieren und unsere Jury überzeugen möchten, bewerben Sie sich jetzt online unter:
https://electricvisionscleve.de/casting.html

Wir freuen uns auf zahlreiche Bewerbungen und darauf, viele beeindruckende Talente kennenzulernen.

Casting call for 1 male actor, with an American accent!
JOSH – 30-40s (Supporting)

Liquor store owner, a sort of friend of Margo’s. Grounded and playful, his warmth is real but insufficient for someone quietly coming apart.  He’s flirtatious without being crude, respectful of strippers and the space they occupy, and genuinely liked by the people around him. His comfort and warmth create a sense of safety.

 

Casting notes: Must feel safe, funny, and grounded. Someone the audience trusts with ease.

 

This is an unpaid filmed table read for pitching purposes.

 

The filming itself will be an hour.

I will be guiding us through some warm ups and brief rehearsal to get comfortable together

Tea, coffee, water and snacks will be available.

 

Sunday Feb 15th 11a-1pm

Central London

Pilot episode -  ALMOND:

Almond is a vulnerable, darkly funny coming-of-age story about stepping out of inherited beauty standards, and refusing to disappear.

 

 

EMAIL: seshedd@gmail.com

topComments.text:
Im more than just the admin. I am unleashing my passion for the arts from rocking the stage to standing in the spotlight, on and off stage, ive had a taste of it all. I've had the privilege of being part of some incredible entertainment experiences. From captivating performances to caring for others, Multi-talented mama on a mission! Actress starring in the YouTube series "The Missi and Kali Show: Noelle and Holly's Christmas Blackout", captivating voice artist lending my voice to the beloved character Carly Standfields in Minecraft Time Agent, the YouTube series I have been making waves in the world of entertainment since 2020 well actually since 2013 when I landed my first project started working toward my goal in 2011. I bring stories to life. and model bringing characters to life  not just on screen and but in print. With features in prestigious publications like Woodbangers Magazine, Celebrity Magazine, My Little Matilda, and The Trendy Icon, I have graced runways for Fairytale Fashions' enchanting prom dress collection back in 2013. Former vocalist with Woodbangers turned background extra and stand-in for awesome productions like "Green Room," "The Librarians," and even made it in a Seattle Super Bowl XLIX commercial!

To fueling my talent with knowledge, I honed my acting skills under the guidance of renowned coach Doug Larson in 2014 while continuing to expand my craft with Allison's acting lessons in 2023 and to continuing acting lessons in 2023 with Timeless Dream Studios. Follow along on this extraordinary journey as I bring characters to life and inspire others through the magic of storytelling. With a background in healthcare nurture the  well-being of others and mixology  creating unforgettable concoctions behind the bar. 

I have a  EFSET certificate in English, and skills in video production, voice acting, photography, modeling, and singing. I am always eager to learn new things, challenge myself, and expand my horizons. I am looking to build my network, meet new people, and work on exciting and meaningful projects. I'm ready to embark on new adventures and bring characters to life.

items.text:
Hi all, new here.

I am a writer and director building a social-first project called Vertical Shakespeare. It is about bringing Shakespeare into vertical, self-shot social spaces like Instagram and TikTok in a modern, accessible way.

I am opening up a weekly, low-pressure challenge for actors called Self Tape Sonnets.

Each week I will post a Shakespeare sonnet on the Vertical Shakespeare socials. You record your interpretation in any style, any accent, any setting, post it to your own socials, and tag @VerticalShakespeare.

That’s it.

It is about play, interpretation, and giving yourself a fresh tape, not about doing it “right”. I will be reposting selected performances to the Vertical Shakespeare feed with full credit and tags.

Think of it as a playground, not an audition.

If that sounds fun, jump in whenever you like. The first sonnet drops soon.

items.text:
[CASTING CALL] This week 11-13 Feb_Blackbird Feature Film

My name is James Connolly, Production Assistant on the feature film Blackbird. We're looking for several Supporting Actors (SAs) over the next few days.

We are re-creating past scenes of predominately Black African/Black Caribbean/Black Mixed Heritage 60s clubs and spaces across the below dates. *Please note, you will need to select either the 60s or 90s shooting days as we cannot have characters time-travelling - Haha. Thank you!

**Wed 11 Feb, 06:00 - 12:00 (est 6 hr @ £12.21/hr) Set in 60s**

**Thu 12 Feb, 06:00 - 09:00 (est 3 hr @ £12.21/hr) Set in 60s**

**Thu 12 Feb, 09:00 - 12:00 (est 3 hr @ £12.21/hr) Set in 90s**

**Fri 13 Feb, 06:00 - 12:00 (est 6 hr @ £12.21/hr) Set in 90s**

**ALL @ The Jacaranda, 21-23 Slater St., Liverpool L1 4BW**

**If you are interested and available, please send the below to jamesconnolly.contact@gmail.com:**

- Full Name

- Age

- Contact Number

- Email Address

- Photograph/Headshot

**(and for our Costume Department)**

- Height

- Top/Dress Size

- Waist Size

- Shoe Size

I'll look forward to hearing from you. If you are cast for one of the shoots I will follow-up with a confirmation email - please await confirmation before you arrive at the location. Thanks again!

Best wishes,

James

topComments.text: Please note all interests will need to email jamesconnolly.contact@gmail.com with the above information - thanks everyone!
Would have loved to do this but unfortunately not available on all dates listed ! Kindly keep me posted with future dates .

items.text:
🎭 CASTING CALL: Annie Meets Frozen ❄️
I’m excited to announce auditions for an original musical, Annie Meets Frozen! This creative show blends the heart of Annie with the magic of Frozen, and I’m looking for performers who want to be part of something fun and unique.
📹 Auditions will be held by Zoom and self-tape submission.
We are looking for children, teens, and adults who love to sing, act, and perform. Experience is welcome but not required!
✨ How to audition:�• Prepare a short song (about 30–60 seconds)�• Submit a self-tape OR request a Zoom audition slot�• Be ready to read lines from the script
📩 To sign up or for details, comment below or message me directly.
Please share with anyone who might be interested. I can’t wait to see your talent and bring this show to life! 🎶

topComments.text: Okay guys... I've done some digging... It would appear Lexi lives in the US and classes herself having special needs and has tried to do this "production" several times before. Please do your due diligence before sending ANY personal details etc

Please do not ask children to DM you for more details... Also provide as much details in advance, What's the company, where are you performing etc... with Children being involved you need complete transparency.

Casting do Fear Factor, czyli Nieustraszeni po polsku

Co do reszty, to zwróćcie uwagę, że zwyrol nadal się nie poddaje, a Wy nadal musicie być czujne. Pamiętajcie, że to nie jest żaden casting, a co zwykła ściema.

‼️ Pilne ‼️
Kochani szukam na plan  reklamy statystów.

Zdjęcia Warszawa

Plan 25.02 lub 26.02 lub 27.02. Termin odległy, ale jutro muszę wyslać propozycję do produkcji.

Najprawdopodobniej jeden dzień będzie dla każdego z Państwa  ale nie wiemy który więc proszę o dyspozycyjność we wszystkie dni.

Wiek 18-60 różnorodność etniczna. 

Mile widziane osoby które zmagają się z niepełnosprawnością, jeżdżące na wózkach itp.

Osoby z bliskiego wschodu.

Proszę o zgłaszanie się osób na adres mailowy-plan@filmakcja.pl

W tytule proszę wpisać daty dostępności 25-27.

W mailu proszę umieścić - imię, nazwisko wiek, tel oraz wyraźne zdjęcia, oraz wymiary. Wzrost, but, pas, talię, r.ubrania.

Stawka 200 za dzień- płatne przelewem.

Zgłoszenia przyjmuje do jutra 11.02 do godziny 14:00. Proszę o zgłaszanie się osób zdecydowanych, gdyż jak Państwo się zgłoszą, będę wysyłać odrazu propozycje do produkcji. Odezwę się do wybranych osób. 

Marta 

Dobrego dnia 😙😙😙😙😙

## [Warszawa] 

Darmowe warsztaty musicalowe dla osób nastoletnich

|Już za dwa dni, w czwartek 12 lutego o godzinie 18:00, drzwi naszej warsztatowi artystycznej Z Miłości Do otworzą się jak szeroko! Zapraszamy osoby w wieku nastoletniem (11–17 lat) na wyjątkowe warsztaty musicalowe! Tego dnia zajęcia są całkowicie darmowe, więc to idealna okazja, żeby przekonać się, jak pracujemy, i dołączyć do naszej niesamowitej grupy musicalowej.
## 
## Śpiew, aktorstwo i taniec. Spotkania odbywają się co tydzień i trwają dwie godziny. To nie tylko nauka, ale przede wszystkim szansa na rozwijanie swoich talentów w przyjaznej atmosferze, poznanie nowych przyjaciół i przeżycie czegoś naprawdę wyjątkowego.
## Nie czekaj, miejsca są limited! Zapisz się już teraz przez formularz kontaktowy na stronie  
## [[www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt](www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt)](https://www.facebook.com/api/graphql/www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt)
## Do zobaczenia

Zapraszamy osoby w wieku nastoletniem (11–17 lat) na wyjątkowe warsztaty musicalowe! Tego dnia zajęcia są całkowicie darmowe, więc to idealna okazja, żeby przekonać się, jak pracujemy, i dołączyć do naszej niesamowitej grupy musicalowej.
## 
## Śpiew, aktorstwo i taniec. Spotkania odbywają się co tydzień i trwają dwie godziny. To nie tylko nauka, ale przede wszystkim szansa na rozwijanie swoich talentów w przyjaznej atmosferze, poznanie nowych przyjaciół i przeżycie czegoś naprawdę wyjątkowego.
## Nie czekaj, miejsca są limited! Zapisz się już teraz przez formularz kontaktowy na stronie  
## [[www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt](www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt)](https://www.facebook.com/api/graphql/www.zmiloscido.pl/kontakt)

Looking for actors/actresses for a production of Cluedo in the Chelmsford area :)
Hi! My name's Ruth and I'm directing a production of Cluedo (3 performances 26th-28th May) in Galleywood in Essex.

It is NOT a paid project - it is an amateur dramatics group that will be putting on a comedic show in May for fun (Cluedo is the British play version of the 1985 Tim Curry movie 'Clue'). I'm in need of actors/actresses who can commit to 2 rehearsals a week who are local to Chelmsford (so bit of a long shot I know!)

So if you're interested in this more low scale show, please reach out to my email address ruthseldenGTG@gmail.com for audition info! :)

**CASTING CALL – SHORT FILM “THE SCAM” (Expenses Paid)**

After a series of slick sales calls, a retired man is moments away from transferring his life savings to an investment “advisor” he’s never met. But when a sudden internet outage interrupts the transaction, the pause shatters the illusion — forcing him to confront truth, desperation, and the human cost of manipulation.

**Peter’s Son (20–30)** – male, techy/geeky

Actor mark your calendars and improve your craft for February 14th—a day filled with creativity, collaboration, and cinematic magic! 

Join us for an incredible opportunity to learn, network, and bring your film aspirations to life alongside fellow passionate creatives. 

This free introductory filmmaking workshop in Los Angeles is your chance to connect with filmmakers who are just as excited about storytelling as you are. Dive into the world of filmmaking, where you'll not only share ideas and inspire one another but also roll up your sleeves and create unforgettable movies together. At Empowering Filmmakers, we believe that everyone has a story to tell. We provide everything you need to make your vision a reality—state-of-the-art cameras, lighting, props, costumes, and even locations. You’ll be amazed at what you can achieve when you work together! Help each other bring your ideas to life as you take turns behind and in front of the camera. This is not just a workshop; it’s a chance to join a vibrant community of aspiring filmmakers who will cheer you on as you embark on your creative journey.

Join us for an incredible opportunity to learn, network, and bring your film aspirations to life alongside fellow passionate creatives. 

This free introductory filmmaking workshop in Los Angeles is your chance to connect with filmmakers who are just as excited about storytelling as you are. Dive into the world of filmmaking, where you'll not only share ideas and inspire one another but also roll up your sleeves and create unforgettable movies together. At Empowering Filmmakers, we believe that everyone has a story to tell. We provide everything you need to make your vision a reality—state-of-the-art cameras, lighting, props, costumes, and even locations. You’ll be amazed at what you can achieve when you work together! Help each other bring your ideas to life as you take turns behind and in front of the camera. items.text:
Landmark gay playwright and author of Bent, Martin Sherman will be joining me on stage at The Two Brewers this Wednesday, as we talk through his extraordinary life and career, and what it’s meant to tell queer stories across the decades.

Born in Philadelphia and educated at Boston University, Martin now lives in London, and his writing has been produced in more than sixty countries. He is renowned for his Tony-nominated landmark play Bent, which opened at the Royal Court and transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, before going on to Broadway starring Richard Gere. The play was later revived at the National Theatre and adapted for the screen in 1998 starring Clive Owen. Bent went on to win the Dramatists Guild’s Hull-Warriner Award, and remains one of the most vital pieces of queer theatre ever written.

His theatre work spans decades and includes Rose (National Theatre and Broadway), Gently Down the Stream (Public Theater and Park Theatre), Onassis (Novello Theatre), Some Sunny Day (Hampstead), A Madhouse in Goa (Lyric Hammersmith and Apollo), When She Danced (King’s Head and Gielgud), Messiah (Hampstead and Aldwych), plus Absolutely! (Perhaps), his acclaimed reworking of Pirandello’s Right You Are (If You Think So) at Wyndham’s Theatre. He also wrote the Broadway musical The Boy from Oz and created a major stage adaptation of E. M. Forster’s A Passage to India (Riverside Theatre and BAM). New work continues, with I’ll Be Seeing You premiering at Pitlochry Festival Theatre in September 2026.

On screen, Martin’s credits include Mrs Henderson Presents (BAFTA-nominated), The Roman Spring of Mrs. Stone, Callas Forever, Alive and Kicking, and The Clothes in the Wardrobe (released in the US as The Summer House). He is currently writing Frank and Percy for the screen, with a major cast including Sir Ian McKellen and Roger Allam.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

🎟️ Tickets are strictly limited to 100, with all profits supporting Queer Theatre’s work nurturing queer talent and telling LGBTQIA+ stories.

🚨🎥 STOP SCROLLING. THIS IS A REAL FILM AUDITION. 🎥🚨
PAID ROLES • SELF-TAPE ONLY • VERTICAL SERIES

What if your livestream… went live again without you touching it?
What if the world watched evil reveal itself in real time?
What if faith became the only weapon left?

🔥 NOW CASTING: THE CULT: LIVE 🔥
A chilling, edge-of-your-seat supernatural thriller made for the digital age.

THE STORY (READ THIS 👀):
Skylar is a famous teenage vlogger living the dream, millions of followers, nonstop views, perfect life. But when she moves from sunny California into a dark Victorian home in Mount Clemens, MI, everything changes.

One night, Skylar ends her livestream…
⚠️ Seconds later, it turns back on by itself.
What unfolds next exposes the house’s paranormal past LIVE to millions around the world.

As the night spirals into terror, Skylar becomes the target of a powerful high priestess from an ancient demonic cult.
Faith, disbelief, technology, and social media collide as good vs. evil plays out in real time with the internet watching.

This isn’t just horror.
This is spiritual warfare in the age of livestreams.

⸻

🎭 PAID ROLES – NOW CASTING

⭐ SKYLAR
• Caucasian female, 18
• Gorgeous, confident, famous vlogger
• Questionable faith

⭐ PAUL
• Caucasian male, 40s
• Atheist
• Skylar’s father

⭐ JOSH
• Caucasian boy, 10
• Skylar’s little brother
• Questionable faith

⭐ DYLAN
• African American male, 18
• Tech geek, atheist
• Skylar’s best friend

⭐ GWYNETH
• African American woman, 40s
• Strong Christian woman
• Dylan’s mother

⸻

📱 FORMAT: Vertical Series
🎬 AUDITION: Self-tape only
💰 STATUS: PAID ROLES

This project explores:
⚡ Social media fame
⚡ Faith vs skepticism
⚡ Ancient evil vs modern technology
⚡ What happens when the internet witnesses the supernatural

👀 If you can command a camera, carry emotional weight, and make us believe, this is for you!

🎥 Submit your self-tape.
🔥 Tag an actor who needs to see this.
😈 The world will be watching… LIVE.
📧 Send all self-tapes to DakeiHarveyFilms@gmail.com

#FilmAudition #NowCasting #PaidRoles #SelfTape #VerticalSeries #HorrorFilm #SupernaturalThriller #ActorsLife #CastingCall #TheCultLIVE

sharedPost.text:
Stage West Playhouse along with director Mathew Root and assistant director Jacob Mandelin are thrilled to announce auditions for "The Glass Menagerie".

IMPORTANT DATES:
Audition Dates: February 6 at 7 PM and February 8 at 1 PM, at the playhouse
Show Dates: April 24-26

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS:
Auditions will consist of cold readings. Video auditions will be accepted until 1 PM on February 8. Video auditions must include your name, address, phone number and email, as well as if you are auditioning for a specific role. Please include any conflicts you have between audition dates and show dates. Video auditions can be emailed to mattroot1274@gmail.com.

SYNOPSIS:
Tennessee Williams’ The Glass Menagerie is a poignant memory play about family, dreams, and the painful tension between illusion and reality.

Set in a small St. Louis apartment during the 1930s, the story is narrated by Tom Wingfield, who looks back on his youth living with his domineering mother Amanda and his fragile, painfully shy sister Laura. Amanda, abandoned years earlier by her husband, clings to memories of her Southern belle past and is determined to secure a future for Laura, whose physical disability and extreme anxiety keep her isolated from the world.

Amanda pressures Tom, who longs to escape his monotonous warehouse job and pursue a life of adventure and writing, to bring home a “gentleman caller” for Laura. When Tom finally invites his coworker Jim O’Connor to dinner, the evening unfolds with hope, awkwardness, and heartbreak—forcing each character to confront their illusions and the limits of their dreams.

ROLES AVAILABLE:
Tom Wingfield (Male, 20s–30s)
Narrator / Son
A restless young man trapped between responsibility and desire for freedom. Tom works in a warehouse to support his family but dreams of becoming a poet and adventurer. He narrates the story from the future, reflecting on the guilt and longing he still carries after leaving his family behind.

Amanda Wingfield (Female, late 40s–60s)  Mother
A faded Southern belle clinging desperately to memories of her youth and the illusion of gentility. Amanda is controlling, talkative, and fiercely determined to secure a future for her children, especially Laura. Beneath her humor and bluster lies deep fear of abandonment and poverty.

Laura Wingfield (Female, late teens–20s)  Daughter
Extremely shy and emotionally fragile, Laura has a slight physical disability and crippling social anxiety. She escapes into her collection of delicate glass animals and old records. Gentle, kind, and painfully self-conscious, she embodies vulnerability and quiet hope.

Jim O’Connor (Male, 20s–30s)
The Gentleman Caller
Tom’s coworker and Amanda’s long-awaited “gentleman caller.” Once a popular high-school hero, Jim is now an ordinary young man with big dreams and relentless optimism. Kind and well-meaning, though sometimes unaware of the emotional impact he has on others.

Questions? Contact the director at mattroot1274@gmail.com.

topComments.text: Did you check any temp agencies?  I know folks who started with them and ended up working at Disney studios...

Honestly no job in the film industry requires a film degree. It requires a good attitude and work ethic. 
I would look into some pa gigs.
If you're looking for consistency then reach out to rental houses for things like reception or even just cleaning cases.
Knowing what you goals are will 10000% garner better advice for you but without knowing whether you want to be an accountant or a contract agent for for dga or in the greens department it's hard to point you in any direction

Hi everyone,

It’s that time of year again! I’m reaching out to see who is available to serve as a **Celebrity Escort / Handler** for our **Oscars Week event on March 12** ** in Beverly Hills**.

**Event details:**
* **Date:** March 12
* **Arrival time:** 9:45–10:00 AM (prompt arrival is required)
* **Wrap time:** No later than 5:00 PM
* **Location:** The Cameo, Beverly Hills

**Role overview:**
You will be assigned **2–3 celebrities for the day** and will escort them throughout the event, including guiding them to the various gift bag tables and activations.

**Attire:**
* All black
* Comfortable shoes (you will be on your feet)

We have some **new and fun activations this year**, and it’s shaping up to be a great event.

If you are available and would like to participate, please reply and let me know. If you have any friends who may be interested and would be a good fit, feel free to pass this along.

Once availability is confirmed, I’ll add you to the list for March 12 and share next steps closer to the event.

Just email me at heathermarianna@yahoo.com if you are interested

Thank you as always—I truly appreciate your help in making these events run smoothly.

Best,
Heather

topComments.text: “Celebrity” and then when you get there it’s some random people and you have to cater to them all night for free 😂😂

Hi everyone,

It’s that time of year again! I’m reaching out to see who is available to serve as a **Celebrity Escort / Handler** for our **Oscars Week event on March 12** ** in Beverly Hills**.

**Event details:**
* **Date:** March 12
* **Arrival time:** 9:45–10:00 AM (prompt arrival is required)
* **Wrap time:** No later than 5:00 PM
* **Location:** The Cameo, Beverly Hills

**Role overview:**
You will be assigned **2–3 celebrities for the day** and will escort them throughout the event, including guiding them to the various gift bag tables and activations.

**Attire:**
* All black
* Comfortable shoes (you will be on your feet)

We have some **new and fun activations this year**, and it’s shaping up to be a great event.

If you are available and would like to participate, please reply and let me know. If you have any friends who may be interested and would be a good fit, feel free to pass this along.

Once availability is confirmed, I’ll add you to the list for March 12 and share next steps closer to the event.

Just email me at heathermarianna@yahoo.com if you are interested

Thank you as always—I truly appreciate your help in making these events run smoothly.

Best,
Heather

## **NON-UNION DYSTOPIAN SHORT FILM**

**This is a non-profit, socially responsible project.**
**All positions are volunteer-based. No one will be paid.**

This is an **experimental, post-war dystopian short film** exploring themes of **witnessing, loss, and survival** through visual storytelling and minimal dialogue.
The project is **non-profit and volunteer-based**, created as a **socially responsible artistic collaboration** intended for festival submission.

**CHARACTERS**
* **War Photographer (Male, 40s):** A quiet witness carrying the psychological residue of conflict.
* **Officer:** An anonymous extension of a system, defined by function rather than identity.
* **Woman (40s):** A civilian confronting personal loss within an impersonal process.
* **Elara (Female, around 8):** A war-displaced child who has learned to survive through stillness and awareness.
* **Arion (Male, around 8):** A war-displaced child shaped by escape, movement, and caution.

**You may submit your CV and photos.**
**250shortfilm@gmail.com**

🎥 **CASTING CALL – Actor/Actress for a Training Video**

Hi there! 👋

At Panda Motion, we are looking for an actor or actress to play the role of a host/narrator in an approx. 25-minute cybersecurity training video series.

**Details:**

🎬 Project: Corporate training video (6-7 episodes, approx. 4 minutes each, 25 mins total) for an LMS platform

📍 Location: Kraków or surrounding area

📆 Date: 1 shooting day (late February / early March - TBD)

📲 Usage Rights: Unlimited time and territory (buyout)

💰 Rate: To be discussed

**Who are we looking for?**

✅ Male or Female, approx. 30-40 years old

✅ Fluent spoken English (C1/C2 level) - mandatory requirement

✅ Professional posture and trustworthy appearance (corporate look)

✅ Experience in public speaking and/or on-camera work

✅ Knowledge of cybersecurity topics is a plus

📩 Please send your applications to: casting@pandamotion.pl
Subject line: “Casting – LMS training”

**Please include in your application:**

Name, age, height, city of residence, and phone number

2–3 current photos (headshot + full body)

Demo/self-tape in English

A recording of a min. 30-second speech in English (any text - read or improvised)

Link to showreel/portfolio (if available)

A brief note about your acting experience

We look forward to receiving your applications! 😊✨

items.text:
Short Film Project - Location Manager / Local Producer Recruitment
About the Project

We are a short film production team based in Warsaw, Poland, currently preparing for a new project scheduled to shoot soon. To ensure a smooth filming process, we are now recruiting a detail-oriented, responsible, proactive, and patient Location Manager / Local Producer to join us.

Responsibilities

1. Scouting & Securing Locations: Identify, contact, negotiate, and secure all filming locations, ensuring availability on shoot days.

2. Talent Coordination: Assist in finding and contacting background actors (extras) and special performers (e.g., specific looks, stunt performers) as required by the script.

3. Budgeting & Quotes: Obtain and negotiate clear cost breakdowns for location fees, talent rates, and other related expenses.

4. Logistics Support: Help source and arrange specific props, vehicles (like long-unused sports cars), or other special items needed for filming.

5. On-Site Supervision: Be present on set in the morning on each shoot day to ensure all arranged resources are in place and functional. After confirming everything is ready, you may leave to attend to other matters but must remain reachable by phone to handle any urgent issues.

Working Mode & Fee

· This is a fixed-fee, project-based position. The total budget for this role is 3000 PLN.

· Pre-production work involves remote and in-person coordination.

· During the shoot, your physical presence is required primarily in the mornings for checks, offering flexibility for the rest of the day while staying on-call.

What We're Looking For

· A responsible, proactive individual with excellent communication skills and patience.

· Candidates with existing local networks or resources are preferred.

· Ability to work efficiently and independently on coordination, negotiation, and sourcing tasks.

· Basic understanding of film production; prior relevant experience is a plus.

📮EMAIL：ron66336@163.com

Get your updated headshots and digitals for 2026 to be properly prepared for castings and auditions!!

Tickets are only $9 

Come in all black form fitting attire, with a second solid colors only natural makeup and hair!

items.text:
UCCS DIGITAL FILMMAKING CAPSTONE FILM AUDITIONS

Our UCCS capstone film production students are gearing up to shoot their capstone short films, and this year there will be a whopping 18 films to audition for! Auditions begin this Saturday, February 14 and continue through March 1. I try to structure the auditions and the film shoots in a way that is as actor-friendly as possible:
* Auditions are held on UCCS campus on the weekends when there is free parking
* I have students hold auditions in groups of 3, so you can potentially audition for up to 3 films in one visit (you will be asked in the Calendly signup to note all of the films and roles you would like to audition for)
* Each film is only allowed one 12-hour shoot day between March 7 - May 3, so you can potentially act in multiple films with a minimal time commitment
* All filming locations must be in or very near to Colorado Springs

COPY OF FINAL FILM AND FOOTAGE

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don’t provide proof that they’ve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. If you have questions about individual films (including whether or not they will accept virtual auditions), please reach out to the contact email on the casting call. If you are having trouble accessing the casting calls, please DM me and I’ll get back to you ASAP.

You can view UCCS capstone films from the past few years at this link:
[https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e](https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e)

Thank you everyone for supporting our student filmmakers!

Para los Iraquíes es súper importante lo arraigado a sus raíces, no lo toman a la ligera. 
Aún así, con las constantes ocupaciones en Irak, el éxodo ha sido masivo, y con él la "Mixtura cultural"

Los cantantes modernos graban en Líbano, Emiratos árabes y con el correr de los años se ha vuelto costumbre las colaboraciones entre cantantes de distintos paises, por lo que encontramos canciones con ricas Mixturas culturales (modernas) y al mismo tiempo con un tinte característico de sus raíces. 

Cómo en este caso, donde Nour Al Zain, Mohammed Al Salim y Daffy -  Nos traen lo moderno y una rica Mixturas entre Irak 🇮🇶 y Kuwait 🇰🇼

Te gustaría Saber más? 
Déjame tu pregunta ❓ 👇

#iraqimood #iraqidance #marielzahraale #bellydancer

Für unseren Kurzfilm „7 Floors to Midnight“ suchen wir einen mutigen Hauptdarsteller.

 Idealerweise bist Du über 40. Herausforderung: Du spielst gänzlich unbekleidet. Wichtig wäre mir, dass Du authentisch spielst. Text ist überschaubar, Emotionen sind wichtig.

Es handelt sich um einen hochwertig produzierten Kurzfilm, der international auf div. Festivals eingereicht wird. Das Ziel ist, min. einen Filmpreis zu schnappen ;-)

Du spielst Claus, den Loser. Insgesamt wirkst Du ziemlich verwahrlost, lebst in einer kleinen, räudigen Wohnung und bist mit Deine Leben unzufrieden - bis plötzlich eine nackte Schönheit an Deine Tür klopft. Mutig weil: Es wird eine (angedeutete) Liebesszene mit Kuss geben.

Es ist lediglich ein kleines, professionelles Team beim Dreh anwesend (Closed Set)

Drehort ist in Göttingen in der Nacht vom 28.2. auf den 1.3.

Hotelkosten, Anfahrt (ICE), ggf. Taxitransfer vom Bahnhof, Catering etc. werden selbstverständlich übernommen. Zudem zahle ich für diese nicht ganz alltägliche Rolle 300,- Euro an Gage.

Bewerbungen bitte mit Bild, Vita und Telefonnummer an sebastian@fesser.tv (bitte KEINE PNs, die gehen hier immer unter!). Stichwort: Claus

items.text: Hallo liebe Filmfreunde, ich bin Gavin 20 Jahre alt und komme aus Stuttgart. Ich beginne im September meine Ausbildung an der Lazi Akademie in Esslingen. Hat von euch jemand Erfahrung damit gemacht oder kennt jemanden der an dieser Akademie studiert hat? Hätte ein paar Fragen dazu. Und wenn jemand jetzt über die nächste Woche Unterstützung am einem Set braucht, schreibt mich gerne an. Ich bin flexibel und immer auf der Suche neue motivierte Filmleute kennenzulernen. Eine Frage noch, wer von euch geht diesen September noch auf die Schule, und hätte Lust sich dort eine WG zu teilen?

Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 7/2026

LITERATURKLASSIKER, GENERATIONSKONFLIKTE UND EIN PREISGEKRÖNTER Ö FILM

Die Romanvorlage von Emily Brontë wurde bereits mehrfach verfilmt. Ob WUTHERING HEIGHTS (2026) ein Hit oder Flop ist, erzählt Ihnen Sarah Fuchs. 

Eine 9jährige wird ausgelost für den damaligen irakischen Diktatur zu backen (EIN KUCHEN FÜR DEN PRÄSIDENTEN) und Sebastian Bezzel kämpft als Schriftsteller mit Generationskonflikten (DIE ÄLTEREN).

Der österreichische Film FEMIZID konnte zuletzt einige Preise gewinnen. Wir konnten mit dem Kameramann,  Bernd Eigner, dazu und vielem mehr ein Interview führen.

Abgerundet wird die Sendung wie immer mit Musik aus den Soundtracks der letzten 85 Jahre.

Mittwoch 11.2.2026 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

items.text:
Actors, be honest for a second. 

Have you ever looked at your headshot and thought:

“This doesn’t feel like me.”

Not bad.

Not unattractive, perhaps very much attractive but does not feel like YOU.

Just…someone else.

A shinier version.

A more “model-y” version.

A version casting will never meet in real life.

And that actually hurts your chances.

Because when your headshot does not look like you, casting feels the disconnect immediately.

They call you in expecting that energy… and a different one walks through the door. 

The gap breaks trust. 

Most headshot sessions create this problem because there’s:

No preparation

No real conversation 

No clarity around what you want to convey to casting

Just “stand there, soft eyes, chin down” and hope for the best.

Hope is not a strategy.

Before I photograph any actor, we talk first and weeks in advance NOT on the day of the shoot!!!

Not to sell you a shoot, but to figure out whether you even need an update or not. 

Sometimes your headshot is working for you, sometimes against you!

Sometimes the issue isn’t the photo, it’s the story your headshot is failing to tell.

If you do need an update, we prepare properly so there’s

X No guesswork

X No over-performing

X No leaving the session hoping there’s one unusable shot

During the shoot, I direct you the entire time, subtle shifts, real presence, grounded energy so the final image feels honest, believable, and castable.

If your headshot feels like a stranger who borrowed your face… that’s your sign.

Comment or DM me: Let’s talk headshots and I’ll DM you so we can chat!

Let’s talk and see if you actually need an update or not.

Laud People leder efter danskere til nyt inspirerende tv-format!
Står du i en uenighed med din nabo, kæreste, ven eller familie? Så har vi den rette hjælp til dig 😊

I et nyt, inspirerende og pragmatisk program forsøger vi at finde en god løsning for alle med hjælp fra professionelle. Programmet er varmt og kærligt - vi tager os af de sager, der er for små, for besværlige eller for følelsesmæssigt rodede til nogensinde at nå en rigtig retssal – men store nok til at true naboskab, venskaber og familiefred. 

Er det dig eller en, du kender, som vi leder efter? Så kontakt mig, Mathilde, på mdalkjaersig@hotmail.com. Send gerne et par linjer om dig selv og den situation, du står i. 

Vi glæder os til at høre fra jer.

items.text:
Casting call for student short film: ‘Don’t Forget the Butter’

We are casting for a short film (7-9 minutes) for our second year project at Greenwich University.

Synopsis:

A man sets out to complete the next task on a bucket list: find the best toast topping. As the story unfolds, it is revealed that the bucket list belonged to his late girlfriend, who passed suddenly and unexpectedly. Completing the list becomes his way of honouring her memory and processing his grief.

Filming: East London, weekend of 14th/15th March 

Important: Please ensure you are able to travel to East London (end of the district line) prior to expressing your interest.

As this is a student production, the role is unpaid. However, travel and expenses and food will be provided. This film will be used within our portfolios - you are welcome to add this to your own portfolio and/or showreels.

If you are interested or would like to hear more, please email your headshot to: lh3568v@gre.ac.uk
